On March 10, 2011, President Obama, the Department of Education, and the Department of Health and Human Services will host a Conference on Bullying Prevention at The White House. The conference aims to bring together individuals from communities across the nation who have been impacted by bullying, as well as those who are actively working to address the issue. Attendees will have the chance to engage in discussions with the President and representatives from his Administration to explore ways in which communities can collaborate to prevent bullying.